.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.045679,0.088542,0.098719,0.10046,0.09836,0.094873,0.092943,0.088234,0.08064,0.07995,0.070302,0.061296],"unified_progress":[0.053185,0.081427,0.088424,0.093228,0.096618,0.094985,0.094031,0.090796,0.086535,0.086665,0.074929,0.059177]},{"section":8,"text":"But the other findings are important too.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042341,0.089661,0.11074,0.11243,0.10239,0.089277,0.085663,0.080249,0.075521,0.082669,0.066643,0.06242],"unified_progress":[0.040806,0.074727,0.086404,0.099493,0.098623,0.094955,0.096179,0.092713,0.08882,0.093213,0.076554,0.057512]},{"section":9,"text":"The pericardial friction rub is a classic sign of pericarditis.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042948,0.086836,0.098104,0.10299,0.10112,0.097806,0.093827,0.086808,0.083179,0.077231,0.066824,0.062324],"unified_progress":[0.042772,0.071176,0.086737,0.10183,0.10093,0.10229,0.098388,0.094144,0.090949,0.082328,0.06959,0.058871]},{"section":10,"text":"Increased JVP could be from fluid overload or maybe cardiac tamponade, but with a friction rub, pericarditis is more likely.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036899,0.079294,0.091498,0.09782,0.098462,0.098497,0.097704,0.091631,0.090501,0.081752,0.072183,0.06376],"unified_progress":[0.037517,0.067334,0.083143,0.094014,0.0999,0.10073,0.099314,0.096201,0.095844,0.087255,0.076337,0.062407]},{"section":11,"text":"The mechanical S2 is expected because he has a prosthetic valve, so that's normal.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046271,0.088332,0.095746,0.099035,0.097139,0.096502,0.093297,0.087912,0.087691,0.078741,0.068092,0.061242],"unified_progress":[0.053063,0.077503,0.090217,0.099254,0.10263,0.099948,0.097862,0.091602,0.089179,0.078,0.065971,0.054772]},{"section":12,"text":"Wait, but what connects all these?","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.33202,0.055247,0.055643,0.063857,0.063281,0.063651,0.059934,0.066548,0.06635,0.061334,0.064146,0.04799],"unified_progress":[0.22306,0.086639,0.068688,0.067346,0.076495,0.073943,0.086327,0.078929,0.073979,0.059341,0.054094,0.051162]},{"section":13,"text":"Prosthetic valve endocarditis comes to mind.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046076,0.097447,0.067363,0.10823,0.10626,0.099215,0.094647,0.087637,0.080233,0.075187,0.069092,0.068617],"unified_progress":[0.055088,0.088265,0.06767,0.094991,0.099094,0.097017,0.094492,0.091674,0.086239,0.081914,0.074942,0.068614]},{"section":14,"text":"The timing is about right\u2014endocarditis can occur weeks after surgery.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039181,0.076774,0.087301,0.093784,0.098071,0.10117,0.097326,0.093263,0.087388,0.085779,0.074438,0.06553],"unified_progress":[0.064508,0.090139,0.088533,0.088758,0.089684,0.092762,0.089187,0.091432,0.085875,0.083062,0.074189,0.061871]},{"section":15,"text":"The symptoms of fever, leukocytosis, and chest pain fit.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031556,0.066119,0.077438,0.085549,0.092632,0.096883,0.10043,0.098241,0.094689,0.092491,0.087915,0.076057],"unified_progress":[0.042021,0.063656,0.074752,0.080213,0.089682,0.096168,0.096522,0.097888,0.098126,0.098051,0.090692,0.072229]},{"section":16,"text":"The pericardial friction rub might be due to associated pericarditis from the endocarditis.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030154,0.065192,0.076923,0.086633,0.092911,0.098079,0.10079,0.097656,0.098957,0.090766,0.08443,0.077513],"unified_progress":[0.035538,0.055792,0.071226,0.081658,0.091135,0.097844,0.098451,0.099046,0.1024,0.098008,0.09116,0.077742]},{"section":17,"text":"Also, prosthetic valve endocarditis is a serious complication.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03082,0.065259,0.078687,0.087